narratives.question_text: How clearly did the instructor define the topic of study?
comments: The class was well defined as to what the goal was and where our knowledge base should be when finished.

narratives.question_text: How clearly did the instructor outline the expectation for the course, classroom activity and homework?
comments: Some of the assignments were challenging because we would get a short overview of a new program, but we would need much more info to thoughtfully use the program to complete the assignment. I would need to teach myself the program and seek more clarification from the instructor and classmates.

narratives.question_text: How well were individual class sessions prepared and presented?
comments: Classes were well prepared but I could have used more clarification on how to use new programs and software.

narratives.question_text: How well did lectures fit within the boundaries of the course?

comments: I wish that we could have spend more time with each of the different software.

narratives.question_text: How available was the instructor for help outside the classroom?
comments: Eric always available for a question, explanation, or guidance on an assignment.
Easy to get a hold of and available for help with class work.

narratives.question_text: How useful were assignments in furthering an understanding of the topic?
If tests were given, how fairly did they measure knowledge gained?
How useful was this course in preparing you for production work?
comments: Have a better understanding of projection engineering and the work that it takes to accomplish it.

I have done some projections work before, but never in the planning stages. Even though this is an intro class, any student that paid attention should be able to successfully set up a projection design rig. I got what I wanted out of the class, which feels great.
This was mostly because I was overloaded and couldn't complete any of the assignments nor give time to preparation for the tests.
I have not had any projections production work
